In this article, Melania Trump reflects on the past year and acknowledges the challenges brought by the COVID-19 pandemic. She expresses her admiration for the unity and support shown by the American people during difficult times. Melania Trump also expresses her condolences for those who lost their lives, including Ashli Babbitt, Benjamin Philips, Kevin Greeson, Roseanne Boyland, Brian Sicknick, and Howard Liebengood. She condemns the violence that occurred at the Capitol and calls for healing and unity in the country. Melania Trump emphasizes the importance of listening to one another, finding common ground, and rising above divisions. She encourages Americans to express their viewpoints without persecution and to reject violence and assumptions based on skin color or political ideologies. Melania Trump concludes by expressing gratitude for the opportunity to serve as First Lady and calls for healing, grace, understanding, and peace for the United States.